your cares : the body's pain A sweet relief may find : But gums and lenient balms are vain , To heal the wounded mind
No more his eyes with fury glow ; But heavenly grief
heavenly hope dispel each dark temptation
while he pours the penitential tear
Music's melting power , Celestial Sorrow rolls her plenteous shower
the rustic measure glide , To quell the dark remains of self-consuming Pride
